## Filter Patterns

### Filter Types

**Principle:** Offer filter types that match the data type of each field - users should be able to filter intuitively.

[REFERENCE] Common filter types by data kind:

```
Discrete (enum/category):
  Status: [Active, Inactive, Pending]         -> dropdown or chip selector
  Category: [Type A, Type B, Type C]          -> dropdown or checkbox list
  Group: [Group 1, Group 2, Group 3]          -> dropdown with search

Boolean:
  Show inactive: [Yes/No]                      -> toggle switch
  Has related items: [Yes/No]                  -> toggle switch

Date range:
  Created: [Start date] to [End date]          -> date picker pair
  Date: [Today, This week, This month]         -> preset buttons + custom range

Numeric range:
  Numeric value: [Min] to [Max]                -> range slider or two inputs
  Score: [1-5]                                 -> star selector

Text:
  Name contains: [input]                        -> text input
  Tags: [multiple values]                       -> tag input with autocomplete
```

### Filter UX Rules

- **Filters persist in URL** - `?status=active&category=featured&page=2` - so the user can share/bookmark filtered views
- **Active filter count** shown on filter button: "Filters (3)"
- **Clear all filters** button always visible when any filter is active
- **Individual filter removal** - each active filter shown as a chip with X to remove
- **Filter changes reset pagination** to page 1 (don't stay on page 5 when the dataset changed)
- **Filter counts** - show number of results per filter value when feasible: "Active (45)" "Inactive (12)"
- **Collapsible filter panel** on desktop; bottom sheet or modal on mobile
- **Preserve filters** on back-navigation (don't lose filters when viewing a detail and coming back)

### Filter + Search Interaction

```
Search and filters are ADDITIVE:
  Search "keyword" + Status: Active + Category: Type A
  = Records matching "keyword" that are active AND in Type A

Clearing the search does NOT clear the filters (independent controls)
Clearing the filters does NOT clear the search
"Clear all" clears both
```

