## Sorting

### Rules

- **Default sort** makes sense for the context (most recent first for activity, alphabetical for directories)
- **Sort indicator** - visible arrow/icon on the active sort column (up for ascending, down for descending)
- **Click to toggle** - first click: ascending, second click: descending, third click: remove sort (or back to default)
- **Sort persists in URL** - `?sort=createdAt&dir=desc`
- **Secondary sort** - define a tiebreaker (e.g., sort by status, then by name within same status)
- **Consistent null handling** - nulls always sort last, regardless of direction

### API Sort Parameters

```
GET /api/resources?sort=name&dir=asc
GET /api/resources?sort=createdAt&dir=desc
GET /api/resources?sort=group.name&dir=asc    (nested field)

Validate sort field on server - reject unknown fields:
  Allowed: name, email, createdAt, updatedAt, status (define per entity)
  Reject: password, token, internal/driver-specific fields, or any field not in the whitelist
```

