## Autocomplete / Typeahead

### Rules

- **Minimum 2 characters** before triggering autocomplete by default. 1 character is fine for small datasets (country codes, stock tickers, short reference lists).
- **5-10 suggestions** for standard dropdowns. Command palettes and admin tooling may show 15-20.
- **Debounce 200ms** (shorter than full search since user expects instant suggestions)
- **Keyboard navigation** - arrow keys to move between suggestions, Enter to select, Escape to close
- **Highlight matching text** in suggestions
- **Show category/type** if suggestions come from different entities ("Record A - Type X", "Record B - Type Y")
- **Recent searches** shown when input is focused but empty
- **Loading state** - subtle spinner in the dropdown while fetching
- **No results** - "No matches for "xyz"" (don't just show empty dropdown)
- **Cache suggestions** client-side for repeated queries (user types "jo", deletes, types "jo" again)

